    "body": "Does it make sense to join 2 chains together? How will people know what the canonical maker dao is or the canonical uniswap router? Once the chain's state deviate, I don't believe there a reasonable way to rejoin them under then same address space. \r\n\r\nTheoretically, this won't be a big deal in eth2. If there is enough demand, we'll just forked chain a shard. That will allow it to maintain it's own address / state space.",
